class Contains

Contains * -- 1 SourceObject
A SourceObject has some Containss. It can have none, and there is no upper bound defined.
A Contains has A SourceObject. It must always have exactly, one, and can never have none. And there is an upper bound of at most one SourceObject.
When a Contains is created, its SourceObject must be assigned. When a Contains is deleted, its SourceObject is not deleted and its list of Containss is decreased. When a SourceObject is deleted, its Containss are not deleted. They are assigned to another SourceObject.

class IsExpansionOf

IsExpansionOf 1 -- 1 MacroExpansion
A MacroExpansion has An IsExpansionOf. It must always have exactly, one, and can never have none. And there is an upper bound of at most one IsExpansionOf.
An IsExpansionOf has A MacroExpansion. It must always have exactly, one, and can never have none. And there is an upper bound of at most one MacroExpansion.
There must always be an equal number of MacroExpansion and IsExpansionOf, connected as Pairs. When an IsExpansionOf is created, its MacroExpansion must be created at the same time. When an IsExpansionOf is deleted, its MacroExpansion is deleted at the same time.
